replies.body:
It doesn't matter that you're "only toxic sometimes", its the fact you are being toxic in the first place, which is what Riot is trying to get rid of. You don't get banned for being toxic for one game, even if you are extremely toxic. Everyone has bad days and riot respects that, so either you've been reported a lot before and considering you've been previously banned it would most definitely not help out your situation.  And people DO get punished for being toxic, like exactly what happened to you. It happens to everyone who is being toxic and gets reported for it, its the tribunal system. How about you don't get toxic and flame people. I report anyone i see being toxic, not because: "oh my feelings were hurt im a sook", its because i dont want anyone else 
to put up with the toxicity in their games. Its OUTSTANDING how many people tend to forget there is a "Mute Player" option right next to their champion on the scoreboard, literally press it and you wont ever hear from them again. Bam, wam and in the bag, they can't flame you. And using the "They flamed me first" excuse is just childish, be the bigger man/woman and get on with it :) 
{{sticker:slayer-jinx-wink}}
